tion time. The experimental results were in agreement\nwith simulations, demonstrating that more than a 50% reduction in scan-time can\nbe achieved by Euclidean-distance-based matching. Conclusion: Optimization of\nthe CEST-MRF acquisition schedule is critical for obtaining the best exchange\nparameter accuracy. The use of Euclidean-distance-based matching of signal\ntrajectories simultaneously improved the discrimination ability and reduced the\nscan time and maximal saturation power required.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Apr 2019 05:57:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-04"}
